This paper is about word embeddings, which are commonly used in natural language processing (NLP) tasks such as text categorization and parsing. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CL (Computation and Language), which focuses on NLP and related topics. The paper also introduces new methods for estimating and evaluating embeddings, which involve machine learning techniques such as clustering and canonical correlation analysis. These methods are relevant to several other sub-categories, including cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), and cs.IR (Information Retrieval). Finally, the paper mentions the use of deep learning, which is a popular approach for NLP tasks and falls under the sub-category cs.DL (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
